Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.79,0:00:02.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eva Heinemann?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.67,0:00:04.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, she was here.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.51,0:00:08.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though she's fallen so far, her\Npersonality hasn't changed at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.97,0:00:12.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, she might have gotten worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.06,0:00:16.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did she mention where she was staying?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:17.64,0:00:19.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, she said she didn't have much cash on her...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.89,0:00:22.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so she was going back to her hotel to get some.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.56,0:00:24.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder how long she'll continue to think\Nshe's a wealthy man's daughter.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.61,0:00:26.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which hotel?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.82,0:00:30.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She said it was the Hotel Staiger.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.82,0:00:32.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if she'll really pay her tab...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.95,0:00:35.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,staying at a third-rate hotel like that and all.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.45,0:00:36.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.87,0:00:39.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.29,0:00:41.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aren't you that man she was engaged to...?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.00,0:00:47.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,H-He was...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:49.47,0:00:52.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello, is this the police?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.14,0:00:54.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I... I just saw that serial killer who was...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.43,0:00:55.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.31,0:00:58.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Have you seen my coat?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.48,0:01:01.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hung it up on the coat hanger by the entrance.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.30,0:02:38.51,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(321,0)\pos(364,365)}Room 402
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.65,0:03:10.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.85,0:03:13.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There should be an Eva...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.27,0:03:16.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a woman named Eva Heinemann staying at your hotel.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.99,0:03:19.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Yes, I'll connect you to her room.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.15,0:03:20.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Please wait a moment.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.70,0:03:21.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.83,0:03:29.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.38,0:03:33.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.17,0:03:37.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm thinking of killing someone.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.13,0:03:40.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Your former fiancee...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.55,0:03:42.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Eva Heinemann.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.05,0:03:44.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.39,0:03:45.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I'm sorry to have kept you waiting.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.76,0:03:48.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}I rang her room, but she doesn't seem to be answering.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.43,0:03:51.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's her room number?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.10,0:03:52.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well I...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.90,0:03:55.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to send her a fax...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.27,0:03:57.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so could you please tell me her room number?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.15,0:03:59.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please, tell me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.40,0:04:02.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}She's staying in room 402.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.36,0:04:03.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Our fax number here is...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.75,0:04:17.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,402...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.76,0:04:25.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's no use.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.80,0:04:29.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Baul can't be reached at his\Noffice or on his cell phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.27,0:04:34.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how long you wait your\Npartner probably won't come.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.27,0:04:38.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,His excuse will probably go something like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.86,0:04:42.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He'll probably say he became Tenma's attorney\Nin order to prove his innocence...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.65,0:04:47.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but he made a complete confession.\NOn top of that, he even escaped.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.37,0:04:49.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He couldn't possibly defend a client like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.00,0:04:52.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He'll probably step down from being Tenma's attorney.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.67,0:05:02.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you going to step down as well, Mr. Verdeman?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.05,0:05:04.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no intention of doing that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.80,0:05:07.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's true that Tenma did escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.89,0:05:09.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Before he escaped...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.35,0:05:11.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wish he would've trusted me, his attorney.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.14,0:05:16.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you trust Tenma, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.98,0:05:21.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you believe what happened in Munich?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.44,0:05:24.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you believe everything that Tenma has told me?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.41,0:05:28.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.62,0:05:32.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure you believe everything?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.54,0:05:37.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I heard the news that Tenma escaped...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.88,0:05:40.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it reminded me of that time.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.67,0:05:44.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The time he disappeared in Munich...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.80,0:05:47.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and tried to kill Johan.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.01,0:05:51.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something is about to happen again.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.97,0:05:53.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's why Tenma escaped.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.64,0:05:57.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please believe in him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.35,0:06:01.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like you believed in your father's\Ninnocence and became a lawyer.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.86,0:06:10.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The phone's been ringing off the hook!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.12,0:06:12.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The media's in an uproar about whether\NVerdeman, the brilliant lawyer...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.79,0:06:17.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,will continue to defend Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.12,0:06:19.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just tell everyone that I don't have any comments.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.50,0:06:23.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,B-But that won't keep the media away.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.67,0:06:27.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then just tell them that we'll hold a press conference...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.59,0:06:31.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,after we've re-examined all the facts and evidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.05,0:06:34.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Until then, don't let anyone into the office.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.14,0:06:36.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, but there's already a guest here...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.85,0:06:39.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.19,0:06:40.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You let someone in?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.81,0:06:42.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not seeing anyone today!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.57,0:06:46.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, I told him that but...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.49,0:06:48.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he forced his way in and said he'd wait.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.49,0:06:50.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just who is it, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.07,0:06:52.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yes...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.20,0:06:54.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's someone from the BKA...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.04,0:06:56.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The BKA?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.67,0:07:05.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Somewhere Over the Rainbow."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.92,0:07:07.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a wonderful song.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.05,0:07:12.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I remember correctly, it was the theme song\Nof the radio station your father managed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.85,0:07:14.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.06,0:07:18.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Lunge.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.44,0:07:20.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,406...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.48,0:07:23.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,405...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.07,0:07:27.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,404...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.87,0:07:38.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Room 402.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.33,0:07:40.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.34,0:07:51.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guten Tag.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.72,0:07:54.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,G-Guten Tag.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.03,0:08:10.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.87,0:08:15.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to the guest staying in this room?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.49,0:08:20.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I came to see the guest who was staying in this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.41,0:08:21.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.46,0:08:23.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thought they had checked out already.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.64,0:08:34.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.60,0:08:35.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no one here anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.52,0:08:40.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eva...!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.56,0:08:43.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Lunge.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.40,0:08:48.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,While I was investigating Tenma's\Naffidavit protocols and such...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.40,0:08:51.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I thoroughly examined your reports.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.53,0:08:54.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your very detailed reports, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.07,0:09:00.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've heard stories of the legal circle's\Ngolden boy, as well...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.08,0:09:01.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Verdeman.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.54,0:09:05.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must've come here after receiving\Nnews of Tenma's escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.83,0:09:07.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.54,0:09:11.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't have any information to offer you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.55,0:09:13.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Escape, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.89,0:09:19.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually I've been on an extended vacation lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.68,0:09:23.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps this extended vacation...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.69,0:09:26.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is also like an escape.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.69,0:09:31.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm, I'm sorry, but I don't have time to socialize, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.40,0:09:35.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, perhaps it's a habit from\Nmy long years on the job...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.16,0:09:39.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but I just can't travel aimlessly around\Nthe world without any cares.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.95,0:09:43.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I came up with a theme for the trip.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.79,0:09:49.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The theme of this trip is this picture book.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.67,0:09:53.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm really sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.13,0:09:54.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I really don't have any time.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.68,0:09:56.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have to ask you to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.05,0:09:58.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, let's talk for a little longer...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.89,0:10:01.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I already told you that I don't have\Nanything to tell you about Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.72,0:10:05.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't come here regarding Tenma's case.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.48,0:10:08.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.69,0:10:13.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I only heard the news about Tenma's\Nescape on my way here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.28,0:10:17.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then why did you come here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.03,0:10:18.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like I said, because of this book.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.28,0:10:23.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've become extremely curious about\Nthis picture book's author.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.50,0:10:27.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, this author had many pen names.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.58,0:10:32.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of them, only the name Klaus Poppe was German.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.00,0:10:34.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So while I was investigating it out of curiosity...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.51,0:10:38.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the name of a certain individual\Nacquainted with Poppe came up.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.76,0:10:39.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A certain individual?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.22,0:10:44.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your father.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.60,0:10:50.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A program named "Fairy Tales of the World"\Naired on your father's radio station, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.77,0:10:54.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,According to the records, in August of '66...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.15,0:10:58.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Poppe's "Where Am I?" aired.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.78,0:11:02.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've also looked through your father's trial records.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.37,0:11:07.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was the greatest post-war case involving suspected\Nspies and shook all of West Germany.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.41,0:11:09.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So what?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.92,0:11:15.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,your father had visited Czechoslovakia many times.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.51,0:11:18.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since it was simply to meet with a picture book author...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.51,0:11:20.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the prosecution didn't mention any of this.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.22,0:11:22.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you trying to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.14,0:11:25.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I just thought that your father...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.77,0:11:29.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,may have been an old friend of this picture book author.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.48,0:11:32.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My father had many acquaintances through his work.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.90,0:11:36.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There were countless numbers of people\Nhe met with to discuss their shows.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.94,0:11:40.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then you're saying they weren't all that close?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.24,0:11:44.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, when I investigated...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.03,0:11:48.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Klaus Poppe would usually hold other meetings\Nat his editorial company-owned house...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.37,0:11:52.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or at an old farmhouse in the Czech countryside\Nthat Poppe used as a resort.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.00,0:11:57.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, meetings between him and your\Nfather were held at a particular mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.09,0:11:59.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A particular mansion?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.72,0:12:03.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was called the Red Rose Mansion.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.47,0:12:08.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The mansion was never used under\Nthe name of Klaus Poppe.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.56,0:12:13.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Whenever he used this mansion, he called himself...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.02,0:12:16.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Franz Bonaparta.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.86,0:12:21.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was a man who held an extremely powerful position.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.57,0:12:24.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the Czechoslovakian secret police, that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.42,0:12:32.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.42,0:12:34.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you trying to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.80,0:12:42.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Son of a spy!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.39,0:12:44.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Son of a traitor!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.68,0:12:47.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Son of a coward!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.81,0:12:56.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go prove his innocence if you're pissed off!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.07,0:12:58.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If the father's dirty, so is the son!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.11,0:13:06.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Son of a spy!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.29,0:13:13.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All I want is to learn about the person\Nnamed Franz Bonaparta.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.50,0:13:15.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know anyone by that name!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.96,0:13:21.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your father met with the picture book author,\NKlaus Poppe, at a particular mansion, correct?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.84,0:13:24.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In Czechoslovakia, in '66?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.47,0:13:27.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A picture book author and a radio station manager.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.35,0:13:29.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's all they were!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.39,0:13:32.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,While he called himself Klaus Poppe...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.52,0:13:36.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the Red Rose Mansion was never used.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.40,0:13:37.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you trying to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.11,0:13:42.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he held a meeting with your father\Nat the Red Rose Mansion...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.66,0:13:45.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that means he wasn't meeting him as Klaus Poppe...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:45.83,0:13:49.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but as Franz Bonaparta.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.50,0:13:53.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Someone from the Czechoslovakian secret police.\Nwith an extremely powerful position.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.00,0:13:55.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That means nothing!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.21,0:14:01.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no interest in whether \N your father was a spy or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.93,0:14:03.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My father wasn't a spy!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.01,0:14:09.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your father must have known who\NFranz Bonaparta really was.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.02,0:14:10.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Irrelevant!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.19,0:14:17.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps your father was aware of what was\Ngoing on at the Red Rose Mansion?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.40,0:14:19.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.78,0:14:21.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My father is innocent! He's wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.90,0:14:23.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.74,0:14:27.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you wish to talk, please contact me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.41,0:14:28.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like I said many times before...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.83,0:14:33.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no interest in whether\Nyour father was a spy or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.88,0:14:39.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just want to know about the person\Nnamed Franz Bonaparta.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.51,0:14:46.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Father was...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.43,0:14:49.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My father was...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.27,0:14:53.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Verdeman, your wife is on the phone...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.06,0:14:58.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.11,0:14:58.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.95,0:15:06.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Umm... your wife is calling from the maternity center...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.29,0:15:19.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.59,0:15:21.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.55,0:15:22.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're finally being discharged?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.92,0:15:23.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's great.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.64,0:15:28.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I'll come pick you up right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.37,0:15:50.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tenma!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.41,0:15:51.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Start the car!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.74,0:15:53.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,C-Calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.25,0:15:54.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen to what I...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.33,0:15:55.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up and start the car!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.67,0:15:58.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.72,0:16:07.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's talk this out.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.39,0:16:08.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, let's calm down.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.59,0:16:10.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me hear what you have to say, Tenma.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.56,0:16:11.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is Eva?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.72,0:16:14.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where is Eva Heinemann?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.64,0:16:16.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.56,0:16:18.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to Eva Heinemann?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.02,0:16:20.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't play dumb!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.44,0:16:22.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know what you guys are trying to do!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.23,0:16:24.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"You guys"?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.69,0:16:26.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't stop the car!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.15,0:16:28.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Face forward and keep driving!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.28,0:16:32.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I know you guys want to kill Eva!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.91,0:16:34.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kill Eva?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.95,0:16:36.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean by "you guys"?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.58,0:16:37.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't play dumb with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.96,0:16:42.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You and that man Baul are working together!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.13,0:16:42.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Baul?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.46,0:16:46.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's the man I shot at the University of Munich library!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.39,0:16:52.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't let there be any more victims!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.22,0:16:53.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Answer me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.18,0:16:54.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where did you take Eva?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.18,0:16:59.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything started when I saved Johan's life.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.56,0:17:03.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Many lives have been taken since then...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.57,0:17:05.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Countless numbers...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.24,0:17:07.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've had enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.86,0:17:09.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There have been too many victims!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.91,0:17:14.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't stop the car!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.20,0:17:16.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is this true?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.58,0:17:18.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm telling you to keep driving!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.25,0:17:21.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is what you said true?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.29,0:17:24.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it true?! Can I believe you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.43,0:17:34.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My father...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.47,0:17:37.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,was suspected of being a spy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.40,0:17:42.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Later, it was established that he was falsely charged, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.36,0:17:46.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he really was a spy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.20,0:17:53.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I believed in my father's innocence...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.07,0:17:55.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,chose to become a lawyer, and studied hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.62,0:17:59.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I learned about it while I was still a student.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.62,0:18:04.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The absolute proof that my father was a spy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.71,0:18:06.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Since then...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.67,0:18:10.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ever since then, I couldn't trust anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.68,0:18:14.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's the "brilliant lawyer who gets all his clients off"?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.60,0:18:16.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The legal circle's golden boy," my ass
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.81,0:18:18.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is so funny!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.06,0:18:20.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Crabbing a guy who doesn't believe in anyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.77,0:18:24.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because I...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.02,0:18:28.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,really am the son of a spy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.24,0:18:36.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I found the notebook...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.37,0:18:41.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I found the notes he'd taken in the 60's...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.33,0:18:44.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything that was written in there...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.83,0:18:46.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Every time I turned a page...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.67,0:18:50.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw everything I'd done out of belief\Nin my father shatter before me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.22,0:18:54.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Without a doubt, my father was a spy.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.47,0:19:03.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Indecipherable codes enumerated there...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.06,0:19:07.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Numerous records of communication with\Nthe Czechoslovakian secret police...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.11,0:19:10.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The mysterious people my father\Nhad come into contact with...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.32,0:19:12.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like Franz Bonaparta...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.53,0:19:16.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did he also mention the Red Rose Mansion in there?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.74,0:19:19.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you know about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.41,0:19:21.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see now...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.46,0:19:28.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That man named Baul probably approached\Nyou because he wanted those notes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.63,0:19:31.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are they now?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.30,0:19:33.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At my house.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.06,0:19:44.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How terrible...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.89,0:19:46.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no doubt about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.60,0:19:49.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was after your father's notes.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.19,0:19:51.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.19,0:19:55.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a letter addressed to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.20,0:20:00.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He probably predicted that you'd come here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.87,0:20:06.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Help me, Kenzou."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.25,0:20:09.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Please hurry and come to the Red Rose Mansion."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.09,0:20:11.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean that Eva's safe?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.71,0:20:13.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.26,0:20:16.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It isn't her handwriting.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.39,0:20:18.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's playing around...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.26,0:20:20.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's toying with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.48,0:20:29.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.94,0:20:32.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's in the pile of old records.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.94,0:20:35.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Somewhere Over the Rainbow."
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.95,0:20:40.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the notebook.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.12,0:20:42.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please take it with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.99,0:20:44.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.29,0:20:47.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,if it falls into the wrong hands, your father will be...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.37,0:20:51.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't need it anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.06,0:20:53.50,Name,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(353,393)}Fr{\fnMeiryo U}ü{\fnNarkisim}hling Maternity and Gynecology Clinic
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.69,0:21:13.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can I believe in you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.49,0:21:17.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything you told me...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.90,0:21:20.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What you're trying to do...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.78,0:21:23.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do anything for you right now, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.04,0:21:27.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,can I believe in you, Dr. Tenma?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.58,0:21:33.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You shouldn't trust people...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.13,0:21:36.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,who wave things like this around too much...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.65,0:21:54.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to believe...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.84,0:22:31.01,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(170,472)}Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.01,0:22:44.44,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(199,475)}Cherish what you know is true in this world.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.01,0:22:44.44,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(201,21)}Ima kono sekai de wakaru koto mitsumete
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.44,0:22:47.40,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(182,472)}Yes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.40,0:23:01.08,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(198,472)}Please believe in the kindness of your eyes
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.40,0:23:01.08,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(199,21)}Anata no hitomi no yasashisa wo shinjite
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.68,0:23:25.94,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(196,473)}Make it home to your land of harmony
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.94,0:23:34.36,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(195,473)}Make it home to your land of purity
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.36,0:23:36.82,Karaoke,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,246)\pos(187,472)}Make it home
